In FastAPI, how route handlers (endpoints) behave in terms of parallelism and concurrency depends on whether they are defined using async def or def, and whether the work inside them is I/O-bound or CPU-bound.
Here are the four combinations of route handlers and how they affect parallel or concurrent handling of requests: async def with async I/O-bound work (e.g., await asyncio.sleep, database calls)
@router.get("/async-io") async def async_io_route(): await asyncio.sleep(2) return {"status": "async io"}
